The Church’s history holds centuries of wisdom—but much of it has remained hidden in archives. Now, a groundbreaking project in Rome is changing that.

Join host Benjamin Crockett in conversation with Father David Nazar, SJ (Administrative Director of the Pontifical Gregorian University) and Matthew Harvey Sanders (CEO of Longbeard) as they reveal how the Alexandria Digitization Hub, the library platform Vulgate AI, and the world’s leading Catholic AI, Magisterium AI, are making ancient texts accessible to all.

Through advanced AI, this initiative is uncovering lost voices, correcting historical errors, and opening new doors for research and education.

What could this new access to Church history mean for you? Share your thoughts in the comments!

